params._metadataServer: API endpoint for badge metadata generation
params._trustScoreContract: The address of the trust score contract
params.name: The name of the NFT

getBadgeData(uint256).details: Get badge data for a token

returns.badgeMessage: The custom message for the badge
returns.badgeName: The custom name for the badge

getBadgeTypeRequirement(uint8).details: Get the required trust score for a badge type

getTierLevel(uint256).details: Get the tier level based on trust score

getTierName(uint256).details: Get the tier name based on trust score

lastMinted().details: Get the last minted token ID

returns._0: tokenId The ID of the minted token

mintWithModel(uint8).details: Mint with a specific badge model

params.badgeType: The badge type to start with (1-10)

returns._0: tokenId The ID of the minted token

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

refreshTrustScore(uint256).details: Update the trust score for a token

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.message: The new message for the badge

setBadgeName(uint256,string).details: Set the name for a badge

params.name: The new name for the badge

setVerifiedStatus(uint256,bool).details: Set the verified status for a badge (onlyOwner)

tokenURI(uint256).details: Generates token metadata URI using off-chain service

returns._0: uri Token URI pointing to off-chain metadata

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
